Primary analyses · DSM Depression
==============================================================================
  Analytic cohort: n = 2,467, incident cases = 463 (18.8%)

--- Between-person analyses ---
  (no multiple-comparison correction across the three rhythm parameters)
  Typical-day mesor         OR = 1.31, 95% CI [1.17, 1.46], p = 1.6e-06
  Typical-day amplitude     OR = 0.90, 95% CI [0.81, 1.00], p = 0.0447
  Typical-day acrophase     OR = 1.09, 95% CI [0.98, 1.20], p = 0.11

--- Within-person analyses ---
  SD daily mesor            n = 2231  cases = 410  univariate OR = 1.18, 95% CI [1.07, 1.31], p = 0.000942
  SD daily mesor            joint with mesor: feature OR = 1.20 [1.09, 1.33], p = 0.000243; mesor OR = 1.34, p = 8.75e-07
  SD daily amplitude        n = 2231  cases = 410  univariate OR = 1.03, 95% CI [0.93, 1.14], p = 0.601
  SD daily amplitude        joint with mesor: feature OR = 1.09 [0.98, 1.22], p = 0.0948; mesor OR = 1.35, p = 7.73e-07
  SD daily acrophase        n = 2231  cases = 410  univariate OR = 1.29, 95% CI [1.17, 1.42], p = 6.76e-07
  SD daily acrophase        joint with mesor: feature OR = 1.29 [1.17, 1.43], p = 8.14e-07; mesor OR = 1.33, p = 1.61e-06

